Flight Kilisa is one of the aviansie bodyguards of Kree'arra, along with Wingman Skree and Flockleader Geerin. She uses melee attacks with a max hit of 365. She also features in the Missing, Presumed Death quest where, alongside Flockleader Geerin, she provided information regarding Armadyl, the aviansie race and the Empyrean Citadel during the quest.

Main drop[edit | edit source]

All bodyguards have a 1/128 chance to roll on to the "bodyguard unique" table, which includes all rare items unique to each faction except godsword shards (which are not unique), godsword hilts (which are only dropped by each faction's general) and Warpriest armour pieces (which can be dropped by all monsters in the same faction). Then, for Armadyl bodyguards, each unique has a 1/384 chance to drop. If no uniques are rolled, then 1,000-1,500 coins will be dropped instead.[d 1]

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 4 June 2013 (Update):
    • Flight Kilisa and Flockleader Geerin now increase the Armadyl kill count in the God Wars Dungeon once again.
  • update 5 September 2012 (Update):
    • Flight Kilisa has been graphically updated.
  • update 28 August 2007 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

Flight Kilisa and Flockleader Geerin speak about Armadyl's return.

  • Prior to the release of Nex, Flight Kilisa was the highest-levelled God Wars Dungeon boss bodyguard.
